            "\n",
            "1. Why RNNs struggle with long-term dependencies:\n",
            "   - Vanilla RNNs suffer from vanishing/exploding gradients.\n",
            "   - Information from early tokens gets lost as the sequence gets longer.\n",
            "\n",
            "2. How LSTMs help with memory:\n",
            "   - LSTMs use 'gates' (forget, input, output) and a cell state.\n",
            "   - This allows the model to selectively remember or forget information over long sequences.\n",
            "\n",
            "3. What attention solves:\n",
            "   - Attention lets the model focus on the most relevant parts of the input sequence\n",
            "     instead of compressing everything into a single hidden state.\n",
            "\n",
            "4. Why transformers are important in modern NLP and Generative AI:\n",
            "   - Transformers use self-attention mechanism (no recurrence).\n",
            "   - They process entire sequences in parallel → much faster training.\n",
            "   - Foundation of BERT, GPT, Grok, Llama, etc.\n",
            "   - Enables massive scaling and incredible performance on text generation tasks.\n",
